<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Berlese created 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Cosmochthoniidae" genus="Cosmochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pterochthonius">Pterochthonius</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Cosmochthoniidae" genus="Cosmochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cosmochthonius</taxonomicName>
, but the resemblance of the two is superficial and holds good in the number of dorsal &quot;coupures&quot; only. As mentioned above, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pterochthoniidae" genus="Pterochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pterochthonius</taxonomicName>
must be regarded as an isolated genus. 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pterochthoniidae" genus="Pterochthonius" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angelus">P. angelus</taxonomicName>
is the type and single representative of it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
